#Text=Wikinews Shorts : April 26 , 2007
#Text=A compilation of brief news reports for Thursday , April 26 , 2007 .
#Text=Dow Jones Industrial Average closes at record high
#Text=on Wednesday
#Text=The Dow Jones Industrial Average closed at an all time record high of 13,089.89 .
#Text=The Dow climbed 1.05 % [ 135.95 points ] at its closing bell .
#Text=On February 27 , the Dow had a record for the worst day since 2001 and plunged over 400.00 points by the closing bell , after the stock exchanges in Asia had a steep loss on the same day .
#Text=Sources
#Text=Vikas Bajaj .
#Text=" Run on Wall Street Sends Dow Above 13,000 " — New York Times , April 26 , 2007
#Text=Ellis Mnyandu .
#Text=" Dow closes over 13,000 " — Reuters , April 25 , 2007
#Text=Anarchist youths attack police station in Athens
#Text=A group of around 30 or 40 anarchists launched an attack against a police station in Exarchia , a busy district in central Athens , in Greece .
#Text=Meanwhile , another 70 hooded individuals launched other attacks .
#Text=They set fire to vehicles , politician ’s offices at the Kolonaki area and various bank departments in Exarhia .
#Text=Greek Riot police responded with tear gas , while the fight between anarchists and the police still takes place in streets around the University of Athens .
#Text=It is believed that the youths launched the attack in order to demonstrate their support to prisoners who started an uprising in three major prisons .
#Text=Another demonstration takes place in Thessaloniki , but without any clashes , so far .
#Text=Sources
#Text=" Incendiary Attacks " — Elliniki Radiofonia Tileorasi , April 26 , 2007

#Text=US Senate bill includes withdrawal date from Iraq
#Text=The United States Senate today passed a spending bill that sets a target date of March 31 , 2008 for a complete pull-out of United States forces from Iraq .
#Text=The House of Representatives has already passed a similar measure .
#Text=The bill also includes US$ 100 billion for the continuing operations in Iraq and Afghanistan .
#Text=US President George W. Bush " will veto this legislation , " said White House spokesperson Dana Perino .
#Text=" The president is determined to win in Iraq .

#Text=Colombia hit by nationwide power-outage
#Text=Colombia was faced with a nationwide electricity outage at 10:15 a.m. local time today .
#Text=Traffic chaos and people trapped in elevators has been reported .
#Text=Hospitals and airports continued operations , using their own backup generators .
#Text=Speaking on local radio , President Alvaro Uribe said , " It appears to have affected all of the country . "
#Text=" The blackout was caused by a failure at an energy substation in northern Bogota .
